items.name: Tanchmix - A BlueMix, Hentai-Diffusion Merge
items.description:
A 0.75(bluemix_v25a) + 0.25(HD-22) checkpoint. So that's 75% Bluemix and 25% Hentai-Diffusion 22. Name is invocative but HD-22 really wasn't specifically made for that, as far as I know.

After 2 months of usage, 1 month of running on this mix and a previous month of a BlueMixV2-HD22 mix, HD-22 doesn't skew the BlueMix artstyle, and works well like most NAI models. Able to run about anything you throw at it.

Both models are kinda cryptic when it comes to their dataset, so I can't really give concrete information. I just found BlueMix to be too rigid in some aspects. So I'm presenting a merge model.

I'm much better with LoRA's and Hypernets than I am with checkpoints, so if you do have some issues with the generations, I may not be able to help much. But always willing to learn something if you've a suggestion!

items.description:
What is Lavender?

Lavender is a semi-realistic model with dark offset compared to Mauve, meaning it is best for images with lights and effects, but also good for general use. It has its own unique aesthetics, and I usually use this if I want a dark-themed or dimmer image. Regarding text prompts, just be versatile and let your imagination flow.Â  And, just like most models it also has few issues with the hands, which can be easily mitigated with this model's inpainting (download separately) or some embeddings. (I still have other models, for some specific arts, yet to be released. Your support will go a long way, and a cup of coffee will keep me awake for many nights. Thank you in advance!)

This version of Lavender does not include a VAE because the goal is for art versatility, wherein, you can use any VAE you like to produce unique aesthetics. Below are the recommended VAEs that you can use with this model to tweak a unique output.

Popular Variable Auto Encoder (VAE)

kl-f8-anime2 VAE (for anime)

anything VAE aka orangemix VAE (for anime)

vae-ft-mse-840000-ema-pruned (for realism)

Sample images above were created with simple text prompts around default settings. More detailed prompts will produce much better results. As for text prompts, just let your imagination flow. One thing to take note, adding keywords like realistic, realism, photorealism, photorealistic, hyperrealism, hyper realistic etc. will make the image more real, and not including any word with real on them will make it look anime-ish.

Settings:

English

This is a LoRa model with a kaijin-style that can generate various tokusatsu-style characters. To use it simply, just use "1kaijin". Since the training material for LoRa is completely 2D hand-drawn (and very flat), please add "realistic" and "photorealistic" to increase the 3D feel. Also, because of this, be sure to use "Hi.Res". I think this LoRa might work well with some 2D models, but I haven't tried it, so I'll leave it to you.

Tips:

  1. Add some characteristic words to generate various kaijin;

  2. The Hires Denoising strength is usually around 0.45, but depending on the generated image, it may need to be adjusted between 0.2 and 0.7;

  3. There's a certain probability of generating a giant monster.

Known issues:

  1. The released model is LoRa, which is a mixture of Locon and a little 3D style, so it's slightly different from the original LoRa. The example images without prompts are all generated by the original Locon, but it needs to be used with other Loras, which is a bit troublesome. So, I'm releasing a plug-and-play mixed model.

  2. Currently, the character feature words are still quite usable, but generally need to write more. This is mainly because the training prompts for this version are generated by Deepbooru and there are hardly any good descriptions of the main features of kaijin. The future version should improve this by adding a manual tagging section.

  3. Because the 3D features are forcedly distorted by training on 2D images, the generalization ability is weaker. If it becomes popular, I will consider distilling it in the future to enhance its generalization ability. So if everyone can generate more images, it can help me achieve this goal faster.

As a TEAM, we prohibit commercial use of it. If you need to use it commercially, please contact us first. However, for personal use, you are free to use it. Thank you.
